Getting my goals straight before going into the new year. 2020 is going to be a big one!

I'm aiming to compete this year in the 2020 Games season and also just trying to stay healthy in doing so. Having goals is a big part of it and having steps to reach those goals is even bigger. 
If you have health goals for 2020 - whether you want to strengthen up, tone down, or have more energy - my biggest tip is to build up a supportive team to guide and help you when willpower gets tough. 
My personal doctor from @steadymd is a key member of my team. I know I can text or call him whenever I have a question about my health, performance, or nutrition. Find out more about how to get a partner for your health for the new year using the link in my bio or steadymd.com/joshbridges
